  "title": "MEP Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Review & understand all tender & contract documents for new fit- out works</li><li>Quantity take off and pricing base on standard market rates</li><li>Prepare checklists, cost analysis & recommendations for tender submission</li><li>Post contract variation evaluation & management</li><li>Attend tender site show round & and provide briefing notes</li><li>Review & prepare M&E costs for miscellaneous works</li><li>Roll out, evaluate M&E subcontractors quotation and prepare report</li><li>Review subcontractor claim and prepare payment recommendation</li><li>Material sourcing and its procurement activities</li><li>Manage, liaise and finalise with subcontractor for variation order and closure</li><li>Attend to Ad-hoc assignment when required</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Candidate must possess at least relevant qualification such as Professional Certificate/NiTEC, Diploma/Advanced/Higher/Graduate Diploma in Engineering (Electrical/Electronic), Engineering (Mechanical) or its equivalent.</li><li>Required language(s): English</li><li>At least 3 Years of working experience in the related field is required for this position.</li><li>Required Skill(s): Client/Consultant Management</li><li>Preferably Senior Executive specialized in Engineering – Mechanical & Electrical.</li></ul>",
